OL,3,CBeing called 'weirdo' by colleague is
OL,4,Ca 'violation of dignity', tribunal
OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FA children's centre worker who was
OL,8,Fcalled a "weirdo" by a colleague has
OL,9,Fbeen paid more than #17,000 after a
OL,10,Ftribunal judge found the comment
OL,11,Fviolated his dignity.
OL,13,FNicholas James, who is autistic,
OL,14,Fcomplained in 2023 to bosses at The
OL,15,FVenture in Wrexham that he could not
OL,16,Fwork properly because of music being
OL,17,Fplayed at the premises which he said
OL,18,Faffected his ability to concentrate,
OL,19,Fthe employment tribunal in Cardiff
OL,20,Fheard.
