OL,3,CBeing called 'weirdo' by colleague is
OL,4,Ca 'violation of dignity', tribunal
OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FChief officer Malcolm King joked to
OL,8,Fhim in November of that year: "Why
OL,9,Fcan't you be ordinary and perfect like
OL,10,Fthe rest of us? But no, jokes aside,
OL,11,Fhaving always been something of a
OL,12,Fweirdo myself, I have some sympathy."
OL,14,FJudge Stephen Jenkins said: "They were
OL,15,Fcomments from the respondent's chief
OL,16,Fofficer, the most senior person within
OL,17,Fthe executive structure of the
OL,18,Forganisation, and were comments which
OL,19,FMr King himself has, on reflection,
OL,20,Fagreed were inappropriate.
